---
id: org.dxos.plugin.inspector
name: InspectorPlugin
version: 0.1.0
---

Real-time AI agent execution inspector. Renders a side panel that shows every
step an agent takes — user/assistant messages, tool calls and results,
reasoning, and per-turn statistics — with the ability to stop the running
process.

## Extensions

The following extension dialects are used in this document.

| Term        | URI                            |
|-------------|--------------------------------|
| `type`      | `org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0`        |
| `feat`      | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`        |
| `test`      | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0`        |
| `component` | `org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0`   |

## Types

```mdl
type InspectorStepType
  literals: user-message | assistant-message | tool-call | tool-result | reasoning | stats | running | turn-start | turn-completed | input-received
```

```mdl
type InspectorStep
  fields:
    id: string                # unique identifier for the step
    timestamp: number         # epoch ms of the event
    type: InspectorStepType
    label: string             # short timeline label
    pending: boolean          # true while the step is in flight
    toolName?: string
    toolCallId?: string
    toolInput?: string        # JSON-encoded tool args (for tool-call)
    toolResult?: string       # tool output (for tool-result)
    error?: string
    content?: string          # full text body (for messages/reasoning)
    tokens?:
      input?: number
      output?: number
    duration?: number         # step duration in ms
```

## Components

```mdl
component InspectorPanel
  desc: Top-level surface rendered as deck-companion--inspector. Reads trace messages from the active space's feed and renders the toolbar + timeline.
```

```mdl
component InspectorToolbar
  desc: Header showing live/idle status, aggregated metrics (tool calls, tokens, total duration), and stop/clear controls.
  props:
    processes: Process.Info[]
    steps: InspectorStep[]
    onStop?: () => void
    onClear?: () => void
```

```mdl
component ExecutionTimeline
  desc: Vertical timeline rendering one entry per InspectorStep with role-specific icons and expandable details.
  props:
    steps: InspectorStep[]
```

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: Live trace
  req F-1.1: Subscribe to Trace.Message rows on the active space's feed.
  req F-1.2: Convert raw trace messages into ordered InspectorStep entries via useEphemeralSteps.
  req F-1.3: Reflect agent process state (RUNNING / HYBERNATING / IDLE) in the toolbar.
```

```mdl
feat F-2: Aggregated metrics
  req F-2.1: Sum input + output tokens across the current step list.
  req F-2.2: Sum step durations for "wall time" rendering.
  req F-2.3: Count tool-call steps for the lightning indicator.
```

```mdl
feat F-3: Stop running agent
  req F-3.1: When at least one process is RUNNING/HYBERNATING, surface a stop button.
  req F-3.2: Clicking stop calls ProcessManager.attach(processId).terminate(). [planned]
```

```mdl
feat F-4: Clear timeline
  req F-4.1: Allow the user to clear the local step list without affecting the underlying trace feed.
```

## Acceptance

```mdl
test T-1: empty state
  given: no agent processes and no trace messages on the active space
  then: InspectorPanel renders with the toolbar in "Inspector" idle state and an empty timeline
```

```mdl
test T-2: live agent
  given: an agent process in state RUNNING and at least one tool-call step
  then: toolbar shows the green Live indicator, the metrics row, and a stop button
```

```mdl
test T-3: post-run idle
  given: no running process but at least one historical tool-result step
  then: toolbar shows the neutral Idle indicator plus a clear button
```
